==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clumps
<hw>Clumps</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A game in which
questions are asked for the purpose of enabling the questioners to
discover a word or thing previously selected by two persons who answer
the questions; -- so called because the players take sides in two
⟦ldquo⟧clumps⟦rdquo⟧ or groups, the ⟦ldquo⟧clump⟦rdquo⟧ which guesses
the word winning the game.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clumpy</ent>⟦br⟧
